This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which are both covered by the Computer Science sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of long short-term memory (LSTM) networks suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper's focus on parsing and dependency analysis could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as these fields often involve similar techniques for analyzing and understanding complex data.
